thread.title: Stricklan homers in Vienna's softball season finale win
thread.title_full: Stricklan homers in Vienna's softball season finale win

author: News Tribune
title: Stricklan homers in Vienna's softball season finale win
text:
Share 
RICHLAND, Mo. — The Vienna Lady Eagles ended their regular season with a 19-4 defeat of Richland on Friday. 
Maddie Stricklan had two hits, including her second home run in as many days. The two-run shot extended her school record to eight home runs this season. Bailey Wilkinson had three hits, five stolen bases and an RBI. Courtney Falter and Jordyn Steffen each had two hits. 
Steffen took the win, allowing one earned run on five hits, no walks and two strikeouts in three innings. Jessica Lineback threw two scoreless innings of relief, allowing one hit and recording one strikeout. 
Vienna (18-4) will be the No. 3 seed when Class 2 District 5 tournament play begins Wednesday at Vienna. 
The Lady Eagles won the JV game 5-2, finishing the year 12-4. ﻿
